name: scripts/docopt/annotate_masses.txt
content:
You can use this script with the following example:
  Rscript inst/scripts/annotate_masses.R

Usage:
  annotate_masses.R [--fil-ann-pre-str=<fil-ann-pre-str>] [--fil-lib-sop-mer=<fil-lib-sop-mer>] [--fil-lib-add-neg=<fil-lib-add-neg>] [--fil-lib-add-pos=<fil-lib-add-pos>] [--fil-lib-add-pro=<fil-lib-add-pro>] [--ms-add-neg=<ms-add-neg>] [--ms-add-pos=<ms-add-pos>] [--ms-clu-neg=<ms-clu-neg>] [--ms-clu-pos=<ms-clu-pos>] [--ms-neu=<ms-neu>] [--ms-pol=<ms-pol>] [--ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms1=<ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms1>] [--ms-tol-mas-dal-ms1=<ms-tol-mas-dal-ms1>] [--ms-tol-rt-add=<ms-tol-rt-add>] [--force=<force>]

Arguments:
  fil-ann-pre-str            List of prepared structural annotations. STRING
  fil-fea-pre                Prepared features file. STRING
  fil-lib-add-neg            Negative adducts. STRING
  fil-lib-add-pos            Positive adducts. STRING
  fil-lib-add-pro            Prepared adducts library. STRING
  fil-lib-sop-mer            Merged structure organism pairs library. STRING

  ms-add-neg                 List of adducts to be used in negative. STRING
  ms-add-pos                 List of adducts to be used in positive. STRING
  ms-clu-neg                 List of clusters to be used in negative. STRING
  ms-clu-pos                 List of clusters to be used in positive. STRING
  ms-neu                     List of neutral losses to be used. STRING
  ms-pol                     Polarity used. Must be "pos" or "neg". STRING
  ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms1         Relative mass tolerance for MS1 in ppm. FLOAT
  ms-tol-mas-dal-ms1         Absolute mass tolerance for MS1 in Dalton. FLOAT
  ms-tol-rt-add              Retention time tolerance for adducts in minutes. FLOAT

  force                      Do not use it. BOOLEAN

Options:
  -h --help                  Shows this screen.
  -v --version               Shows version.

name: scripts/docopt/annotate_spectra.txt
content:
You can use this script with the following example:
  Rscript inst/scripts/annotate_spectra.R --fil-spe-raw data/source/examples/spectra.mgf --fil-lib-spe-pos data/interim/libraries/spectra/is/lotus_pos.rds --fil-ann-raw-spe-spe data/interim/annotations/example_spectralMatches.tsv.gz --ms-tol-mas-dal-ms2 0.01 --ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms2 10 --ann-thr-ms2-sim-ann 0.0 --ms-thr-ms2-int 5 --ann-ms2-app false

Usage:

Arguments:
  ann-ms2-app                Perform approximative matching without precursor matching? BOOLEAN
  ann-thr-ms2-sim-ann        Similarity threhsold for annotation. FLOAT

  fil-ann-raw-spe-spe        List of spectral matching results. STRING
  fil-lib-spe-neg            List of negative spectral libraries. STRING
  fil-lib-spe-pos            List of positive spectral libraries. STRING
  fil-spe-raw                Raw spectral file. STRING

  ms-pol                     Polarity used. Must be "pos" or "neg". STRING
  ms-thr-ms2-int             Intensity threshold for MS2. INTEGER
  ms-tol-mas-ppm-ms2         Relative mass tolerance for MS2 in ppm. FLOAT
  ms-tol-mas-dal-ms2         Absolute mass tolerance for MS2 in Dalton. FLOAT
  ms-tol-rt-min              Retention time tolerance in minutes. FLOAT

Options:
  -h --help                  Shows this screen.
  -v --version               Shows version.

name: scripts/docopt/create_components.txt
content:
You can use this script with the following example:
  Rscript inst/scripts/create_components.R --fil-net-spe-edg-pre data/interim/features/example_edges.tsv.gz --fil-net-spe-com-raw data/interim/features/example_components.tsv.gz

Usage:
  create_components.R [--fil-net-spe-edg-pre=<fil-net-spe-edg-pre>] [--fil-net-spe-com-raw=<fil-net-spe-com-raw>]

  wei-che-22                 Score for a chemical NPC superclass match. FLOAT
  wei-che-23                 Score for a chemical NPC class match. FLOAT

  compounds-names            Report compounds names. Can be very large. BOOLEAN
  force                      Do not use it. BOOLEAN
  high-confidence            Report high confidence candidates only. BOOLEAN
  remove-ties                Remove ties. BOOLEAN
  summarise                  Summarize results (1 row per feature). BOOLEAN

Options:
  -h --help                  Shows this screen.
  -v --version               Shows version.
